@startuml fig-rpc-call-types
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title RPC Call Types (gRPC Streaming Models)

participant "Client" as C #FFE0B2
participant "Server" as S #C8E6C9

== 1. Unary RPC ==

C -> S : single request
S --> C : single response

== 2. Server Streaming ==

C -> S : single request
S --> C : response chunk 1
S --> C : response chunk 2
S --> C : response chunk N
S --> C : stream end

== 3. Client Streaming ==

C -> S : request chunk 1
C -> S : request chunk 2
C -> S : request chunk N
C -> S : stream end
S --> C : single response

== 4. Bidirectional Streaming ==

C -> S : request chunk 1
S --> C : response chunk 1
C -> S : request chunk 2
S --> C : response chunk 2
C -> S : stream end
S --> C : stream end

legend right
  Unary: one request, one response (most common).
  Server streaming: one request, multiple responses.
  Client streaming: multiple requests, one response.
  Bidirectional: both sides stream concurrently.
  This seminar focuses on unary RPC.
endlegend
@enduml
